Statement Lines and Comments
\f2\b0          \
\
Every 7eleven statement consists of one or more lines in the source file. (There cannot be multiple statements on a single line.) If more than one line is required, a backslash character (\\) can be inserted anywhere between the last code character on the line and either the end of the line or the start of any comment on the same line.  Except in strings (see below), a semicolon character (;) starts a comment which extends to the end of the line. \
\
Every source line can additionally have an optional hex address in triangular brackets, e.g. <7F02>, before the first statement token. This address is completely ignored by the compiler. \
