After removing comments and splicing together all source lines that make up a 7eleven statement, the line is split into tokens. Unless the statement is a string definition (.STR, \'85) white space is used to separate the tokens. If the first token ends with a colon character (:), it is interpreted as a label definition. The next token is the operation, and all following ones are operation arguments. \
\
